<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="65" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,152,514]" pageId="4" pageNumber="65">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,341,301,327]" pageId="4" pageNumber="65">Etymology:</emphasis>
Lofo. A Greek noun meaning “panache,” which refers to the shape of the setae that cover several portions of the body.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,152,514]" pageId="4" pageNumber="65">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,444,375,401]" pageId="4" pageNumber="65">Comparative notes:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[452,679,376,401]" class="Insecta" family="Notonectidae" genus="Martarega" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lofoides">
<emphasis box="[452,679,376,401]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="65">Martarega lofoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished by the presence of tuft-like setae in the apex of antennal segment II, middle coxae (
<figureCitation box="[572,644,413,439]" captionStart="FIGURES 2 – 6" captionStartId="3.[151,273,1954,1978]" captionTargetBox="[241,1324,220,1928]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[205,1381,194,1933]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2 – 6. Structural details of Martarega new species. 2 – 3, M. awa, 2 hemelytron of female, 3 male genital capsule; 4 – 6, M. lofoides, 4 hemelytron of female, 5 middle leg, omitted tarsus, 6 male genital capsule." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/197020/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="65">
Fig. 
<number box="[628,644,413,439]" pageId="4" pageNumber="65" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
), and pro-pleural margin; the characteristic pattern of the stripes of the female hemelytra (
<figureCitation box="[416,489,450,476]" captionStart="FIGURES 2 – 6" captionStartId="3.[151,273,1954,1978]" captionTargetBox="[241,1324,220,1928]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[205,1381,194,1933]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2 – 6. Structural details of Martarega new species. 2 – 3, M. awa, 2 hemelytron of female, 3 male genital capsule; 4 – 6, M. lofoides, 4 hemelytron of female, 5 middle leg, omitted tarsus, 6 male genital capsule." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/197020/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="65">
Fig. 
<number box="[472,489,450,476]" pageId="4" pageNumber="65" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
), and the shape of the male genital clasper (
<figureCitation box="[1009,1082,450,476]" captionStart="FIGURES 2 – 6" captionStartId="3.[151,273,1954,1978]" captionTargetBox="[241,1324,220,1928]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[205,1381,194,1933]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2 – 6. Structural details of Martarega new species. 2 – 3, M. awa, 2 hemelytron of female, 3 male genital capsule; 4 – 6, M. lofoides, 4 hemelytron of female, 5 middle leg, omitted tarsus, 6 male genital capsule." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/197020/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="65">
Fig. 
<number box="[1065,1082,450,476]" pageId="4" pageNumber="65" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
). The female has a long spine on the lateral margin of the middle femur (
<figureCitation box="[650,722,488,514]" captionStart="FIGURES 2 – 6" captionStartId="3.[151,273,1954,1978]" captionTargetBox="[241,1324,220,1928]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[205,1381,194,1933]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2 – 6. Structural details of Martarega new species. 2 – 3, M. awa, 2 hemelytron of female, 3 male genital capsule; 4 – 6, M. lofoides, 4 hemelytron of female, 5 middle leg, omitted tarsus, 6 male genital capsule." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/197020/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="65">
Fig. 
<number box="[705,722,488,514]" pageId="4" pageNumber="65" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
